8:
I believe we've just about covered
the shallows. Shall we head back
soon—
17:
The Kaleidoscope's shaking! How
could this be happening here of all
places—
43:
Welcome to Starview Village. Please
relax. You're safe now.
46:
Hm, let's see if your memory's intact.
Can you tell us your name?
54:
I'm Stella. The others are Alk, Light,
and Nimbus. We are not your
enemies.
55:
We found you collapsed in the
Kaleidoscope. Do you remember
how it happened?
58:
No idea. I just remember I was going
somewhere when my head
suddenly started to hurt.
61: Are you the ones who saved me?
65:
Mm-hm! Only friendly faces here, so
there's no need to be alarmed.
69:
Maybe you can come on my
adventure.
75: Hooray! You just made my day!
91:
Why are you backing away? You
promised me...
96: What the hell is your deal?!
98:
You promised to come on my
adventure... You tricked me...
99:
How could you... Anyone who comes
on my adventure has to die first.
104:
I believe you're mistaken, Luna. Once
a person dies, that's—
116:
How do you do it? I wish my doll
could talk too.
122: That's right! I'm a talking doll!
134: Oh... already dead? Do tell me more.
138:
I used to be human, but then the
Lord of Shadow plucked my life
away... I'm essentially a living corpse
now!
141: Hm, I'm not sure I get it.
149:
Come now, did you really have to
wake me up just for this?
152:
It shames me to ask, but... Could you
just go along with my story, Regitare?
156:
Regitare. Yes, that is I. As if my
beautifully decrepit form did not
already give it away, I am indeed as
dead as can be.
158:
The talking doll you see beside me is
equally keen on pushing up daisies.
He's what you might call a
wandering spirit doll.
162:
Um... So you'll come on my
adventure then?
165:
I don't see why not. I can be your
companion for as long as you wish
it. Of course, that goes for the doll as
well.
169:
Hooray! I have new friends for my
adventure!
173:
Will the rest of you be coming along
too?
178:
The others, erm... I'm afraid they
need more time to die! They're not
ripe for adventure just yet!
182:
I must concur. 'Tis indeed often
better to live a little before kicking
the unholy bucket.
185:
Eh, no matter. I made two new
friends at least!
189:
And as friends, we need to set one
important ground rule: no going out
alone. Sound good to you?
196:
Seriously, Light... How long do you
think you can keep up the charade?
199:
She's still young... She has much to
learn.
205:
Let's leave it at that, lads. This was
the best decision given the
circumstances.
209:
Teehee! The more the merrier for my
adventure!
